Excellent emulator marred by absolutely insane DRM. The app seems to require that you connect to the internet every time you start it so that it can verify that you have a valid license from the publisher. If an internet connection is not available, it will tell you that you failed the "license check" and will severely limit the speed of the emulation, making even quite old DOS programs essentially unusable. If you successfully verify the license and then close and restart the app for any reason (e.g. you need to use a different app for a while) it will run the check again the next time you start it, even if it's only a few minutes later, and if you don't have internet access at that point, it will again conclude the license check was "failed" and clamp down on the speed of the emulation. This was *severely* inconvenient to me on a recent trip when I didn't have a consistent usable internet connection for my device. I was unable to use this app on several occasions when I really wanted to. This draconian DRM absolutely ruined my experience with DosBox Turbo.  Two stars instead of one because I have to admit that when I do have internet access on my device, this emulator works well.

Great emulator, probably the best however as always if you are new to emulators it's pretty tricky to get games working is you are NOT rooting from a pc.    If you are struggling I can only suggest downloading a file manager and creating a folder called dos on to your Sdcard then changing the directory within dosbox from:  storage/emulator/0/downloads  To    storage/emulator/0/dos  Then create separate folders within /dos for your separate games (making sure the folder names are no longer than 8 letters long) and move your downloaded games into the folders.   Open dosbox and C drive should be running from your new dos directory, from here you type the command:  cd dune (example of file name within dos)   And then type the games execution file, example   duneprg.exe (for dune)  And off you go.  You will have to look through the games folder and work out the execution file yourself.    I hope that helps someone because this is an amazing emulator.

I commend Dosbox Turbo of having the easiest way of installing Windows and supporting 3Dfx/voodoo. Definitely brings a lot of titles from the early 2000 and before being able to run. Sadly the UI is complicated beyond belief and not very user friendly, controller/keyboard wise especially. Magic Dosbox allows you to change settings in the fly,have widgets/keyboard keys anywhere on screen and highly configure to your needs, and has a completely transparent keyboard built in - all this lacking in Dosbox Turbo. You also almost never see DOS (only for installations) or require so much command prompts in Magic Dosbox - something you HAVE TO in Dosbox Turbo. If the UI and control options had a complete overhaul, this would be awesome.

Neat little tool to get your tablet to run old dos games. Don't expect a hand-holding experience; you will have to look it up and it might take about an hour to set up the first time, but it will work. Currently using it to play Master of Magic on it and, besides a few control hardships, it's a pretty fun experience.  There are also a lot of people complaining that the product has been abandoned by the devs. Ironic, seeing as the latest version of DOSbox is from 2010.  There are other free versions around as well, if you'd rather not pay for it, but if you do, expect a very good experience yet slightly difficult learning curve.   My only major beef with it is the top-bar on the screen containing the keyboard/joystick/buttons shortcuts and how difficult it can be at times to hide after it's been displayed during gameplay.

However, this latter also applies to UAE4All2 and WinUAE is a solid emulator on a desktop, so I get the distinct feeling that it's Android and the way it handles things like the filesystem and virtual keyboard that screws things up. How could I stop the quick menu from showing up every time I double tap left key?
replyContent: If the default Dpad mappings (left,right,down,up) got erased, the direction movement will no longer be captured by DosBox Turbo and will instead fall through to the Android OS.  The Android OS will open sliding drawers with a left movement.  The easiest way to resolve this issue is to use the "reset to default" setting in DosBox Turbo.

content: Emulation works well with dos games unfortunately compatability with nvidia shield controller is garbage. Giving up. Too many headaches, better to use dosbox on PC.

Anything DOSBox PC can do, DOSBox Turbo can do just as well. I haven't found a game yet that this thing doesn't run flawlessly, or near enough.  Sierra/Lucas-style point-and-click adventures are a perfect fit for this app when using the Absolute Mouse Tracking feature--it's as if they were specifically designed for touchscreen devices. (For games that don't get along with Absolute Tracking, use Relative Tracking to place the cursor in the bottom-right corner of the screen, then switch to Absolute. Should function properly now.)

I bought this version of DOSBox because of how nice the user interface is. It was not until I had time later to try to use our old DOS programs to talk to our field equipment with that I realized the standard DOS serial ports had been removed. They work on other DOSBox implementations. That was the one feature we really needed. I hope the developer will consider adding serial ports back in a future releases. Alot of people need to use DOSBox for more than just playing games.

This emulator just has too many flaws:  - Games stutter on a Nexus 7 (2013) even when using only 7.000 cycles - a far cry from emulating a P66 which the website claims. Virtually no game is smooth or playable. And no, setting cycles to Auto doesn't help - stutters happen no matter what I do.  - The on-screen joystick only works properly if the game supports it - which lots of DOS games don't. You can't bind the on-screen buttons to keyboard commands either - huge missed opportunity since it makes most games unplayable without a physical keyboard.  - When using a physical mouse, you'll have both game and Android cursors on the screen at the same time, both moving independently. When the Android one hits the edge, the game cursor stops dead. Plz hide Android one and make the game one continue to move when an edge is hit because many mouse games are unplayable now or extremely frustrating.  - screen scaling should be allowed multiplication - 2x, 3x, 4x - like in real DOS. Right now it's 1:1 or full screen. Smaller issue but still worth mentioning.  I'll adjust the score if things get fixed - the stutters & mouse being the biggest flaws.
replyContent: Sorry you are having problems.  Feel free to email us and we will try and help you with the stuttering you are experiencing.  Most games play smoothly when using "Auto" cycle mode, which is what we recommend using.

Superb app!  Not much different than the PC version.  Users with Samsung devices should take note (esp. Galaxy Note 8.0 and Galaxy S4 users).  Samsung's horrible default software keyboard associates itself to any Bluetooth or hardware keyboard, which prohibits simultaneous keyboard inputs.  Samsung is not nice about allowing users to associate other software keyboards (i.e., Google Keyboard) with Bluetooth keyboards, forcing the user to stick with the default Samsung keyboard everytime a BT keboard is connected.  To get around this, connect your BT keyboard, then change the default keyboard to the Google keyboard.

This is an insanely good/polished emulation app. It is absolutely insane on my TF700 with the KB dock and PS3 game pad. It is like a retro gamers play ground. It supports the keyboard, mouse/touchpad, and external joypads on the TF making it an old school DOS gamer's dream machine. The free Manager program add-on is an excellent front end and really makes this a complete package. Everyone who has done retro gaming and DOS gaming knows that configuring DOS programs is a pain but with the front end, you set it up once and forget it.   This app was worth every penny several times over and the developer regularly updates and improves it. One of my favorite purchases for Android.

Absolutely flawless DOS emulation on the go. Still learning as I go with it, but having a blast doing so. Some of my best gaming experiences came from playing a lot of the old school adventure point and click titles. I cannot wait to test Phantasmagoria on it. Thank you so much! Im also using this on my EVO LTE.

I bought this, so I could run my favorite, old games. Of course, I grew up using Windows 3.1, 95, & 98se, so I configured everything to boot into Windows. When I managed to get SimCity 3000 Unlimited installed and realized it actually ran, I was in heaven. It may be slower than an old Pentium, but it's very playable. The music/sounds are garbled in Windows, but it'll take faster, more efficient ARM processors to properly run an x86 emulator.
Best dosbox for android I've found.
I can roast retros any where I go. Cheers, mate.
Superslow and choppy sound in both experimental turbo and normal mode. How can it cost anything?
Runs pretty much everything you throw at it.

nice port, can map controls to keyboards or gamepads and easier to use than the windows version with the built in menus and automatically mounts your c drive. not quite as fast as the windows version, but a darn site faster than the other dosbox ports on playstore, and handles most games that require a 486 or less, games that required or recomended  pentium run rather choppy tho eg quake isnt really playable on lowest res and half screen on my tegra iii transformer pad...don't even try tomb raider lol...so i think emulation is of a 486dx4/100 at best, no midi support so if a game you want to play uses midi be aware! There was some crashing issues with the new Asus transformer pads but that seems to have been fixed with a firmware update (at least it has on mine)
Finally night trap on the go. An excellent app.

i'm a complete dosbox n00b but for the sake of older titles like starfleet 1 and tyrian 2000, i decided to bite the bullet and give it a shot.  i started playing with dosbox on the pc and at the same time, i got dosbox turbo for the nexus 7.  as a complete beginner, i found that i got much farther much faster using dosbox turbo.  in fact, i learned most of the salient point about dosbox in general by using dosbox turbo.  and the developer is really quick to respond with bug reports and is really nimble with development.  fantastic app, fantastic support and great great performance.

Got all of my old flight sims out. Falcon to Red Baron to EF2000. All work with no problems and the amount of settings allow each one to be tweaked to perfection.  The later sims are more processor intensive.  So EF2000 for example has to be set to low detail on a Nexus 7 but still works. Maybe its time to throw out my physical PC/XT??? (wife is cheering in the background) Thanks. Well worth the price. :)
Dunno if you remember me, but the joystick in It Came From the Desert works perfectly now since the rewrite. Ace job mate
I was struggling to find a way to play Destruction Derby with an acceptable framerate. Problem solved!
Every DOS program I try to run won't render properly on my Galaxy S3 running CM10.1
replyContent: Please contact us.  I'd be happy to help you figure out what is wrong.

content: I can not manage to mount a drive.. I got games folders on the sd card but I can't find any drive letters so I know what to mount.. The guide doesn't really help there, unless I'm missing something obvious.

Playing some good old DOS games brings back memorys. and playing them on a tablet attach to a keyboard to make it look like a mini laptop made me almost forget that i am playing it on a tablet and not on a computer :-)
Been able to play several intensive games such as duke nukem 3d, dungeon keeper, theme hospital, and many others.

In landscape mode i did not see the action bar to bring the keyboard up. I learnt that you swipe down from the top of the screen to activate it.  Now I can use this app, it seems great. Thanks to the dev for responding to my comment on here since my email did not go through.
After I took the time to reconfigure my games, everything works better compared to the previous version. I can even use auto cycles without sound problems.   Ps: thanks for the very fast response!
I can't seem to find the button to change settings inside the app. Im running it on a galaxy note 10.1  Edit...stupidbme, i figured it out. This works great.
Thanks for frequent updates! I don't really play dos games on my phone. Mostly just for fun. Is there a list of configs or import from dfend feature?

So far it works pretty well, I really wanted to play "blood" on my phone but not really playable, tested it out on 3 different phones. This emulator still gets updated and probably the best one on the market  Edit-the new update is beyond great, it seems perfect, gonna test more games on it

Got windows 95 working on this, was a fun exercise, I wish there was a setting to use the old menu, not only because it was better at the bottom but also because it seemed less laggy to access the menu with it... Good stuff either way!

Joystick seems broken on latest release for some games? When playing 'moonstone' its as if the virtual d-pad is always being held down to the left making it unplayable? Worked fine previously but no options seem to fix this? Hopefully this can be updated as I need my moonstone fix? Lol I also can't get 'turrican 2 the final fight' to install but that might be me? Anyway keep up the good work as many games run fine.
I couldn't work out how to use cursor keys but the app's author got in touch to help me out which was great of him.
old games and old software run better than they do on my 486 dos machine.
Update to fix a  updated  problem so quickly that i just notice it. Thanks a lot for  supporting my 2yr phone.
no video..just the icons floating up top... just bought it yesterday and now can't use it....
I cannot find tandy sound emulation.  This is one of the main features I use on the pc version.

I was a little unsure about this app before I bought it, since my preferred mouse controls were listed as "experimental", and since the website said the initial focus app was "fully supported external keyboard and mice", whereas I want to play without any external devices. But this app has a very comprehensive set of options for configuring "soft" keyboard and mouse! I tried AnDosBox at first, and I couldn't get it to do what I wanted; could barely get it to take arrow key input. Here, I can configure the keys of a gamepad to do exactly what I want; I don't have to exit the app to change my keyboard input; I can even resize the game screen so the keys don't cover up where I have to click, and make the keyboard appear/disappear with a gesture (instead of several button presses each time). DosBox Manager makes this even better, since I can have per-game customized configurations, and launch a game with a single click.
I love it! Now I can play all my favorite dos games on the go.
Tried Settlers 2, Alley cat and The Incredible Machines 2. All worked perfectly. Thumbs up, guys. Old hit games are back! Now even on Nexus 7
Live this!! Just wanna say that there's no option for mapping the backspace key. Hopefully next update =)

I have tried aDosBox before buying this app and there is absolutely no match between the two. DosBox Turbo is faster, handles the majority of the games I throw at it, has far more options and customization. I find really useful that the mouse position can be set as absolute having the pointer exactly at your fingertip, good when you play games as Them Park. All settings you may thing of are available! Also I would like to thank the developer as he is really responsive and polite. A must have for all of us that know the meaning of CGA/EGA :) By the way I am running this on NEXUS 7.

Everything runs that's not a question, but I wasn't able to actually play anything. I've tried all possible settings but the sound always cracks and skips, and everything is just dead slow :( It was the same with the stock rom and now is the same with the custom rom with the tegra 3 oc'ed to 1.7ghz. It's very dissapointing cause I thought I'll be able to play dos games at least to the 486 era.

Best dosbox for droid. On my htc one x I was frustrated by not having any cursor keys on the default kbd. Htc one x has no menu button so DBT put one @ the bottom of the screen, taking up the room for the cursor keys. There is a setting to make the recent apps button act like a menu button on a long press. Problem solved.
Runs fallout. What more can I say?

Running everything smooth so far. I just wish it had built-in on-screen, mappable buttons, so I wouldn't have to keep switching input methods all the time. It's a pain if you don't have physical buttons.

Great App, would give 5 stars it it would stay open in the background when you text or take a call or use another app. I suggest mapping the right and left mouse buttons to the volume buttons rather than try to use the tap/double tap for mouse buttons.
Fantastic piece of work. Works like a charm, has played everything I've thrown at it without a hitch.
That's it, I love it :)
Excellent port but remove online verification. You have my money. Don't limit what I've paid for when my tablet is offline.
This emulator is working very smooth on MK802 but the mouse capture is so buggy! For playing games on Gamepad or Keyboard is so awesome but on Mouse is a terrible experience.  Please fix it!

I've put on doom, blake stone, chex quest, and some other games without much trouble. There isn't much support for game settings because every device is so different but it is just so much fun to tinker with.
This is really fast, much faster than other DosBox ports in Google Play. Still got some low framerate in Lion King, but it's still way better. Thanks

Got fallout up and running :) that alone is amazing. However the on screen joystick could use some work. Until then I'll stick with click games  EDIT: Trying to get doom/hexen working with a ps3 controller. apparently the right analog isn't supported. Bummer, maybe include this feature in a future update?

after debugging with the dev :3 if you have a A13 tablet. and you get "Unforantly dosbox has stoped " you need a lil handiwork to get it working on the ARMv5 libs  (you nee dto unpack the APK, copy libs from it to the device's /data/data/com.fishstyx.dosbox/libs and run thru DosBox Manager and "Disable Optimizations" real nice the dev is and took time to help find out why it was crashing on my device!
I regularly run tools, games and even Win 3.1 (seriously... Its handy on a phone) on both a nexus 7 and s3.  Speed and customizability are both excellent.
It works, to an extent, however I couldn't manage to get into any game because my Nexus 7 freezes or resets.

The mouse emulation functions badly, at least for my air mouse (Android 4.1). The cd-rom emulation is not as good as the desktop version, which means that I cannot run my favourite program that must be fueled from cd. However, I am able to run Win3.1, after having installed soundblaster, which is impressive.
Best dos emulator I've found. Spent the afternoon happily playing System Shock
Fantastic Emulator. Updated frequently. It runs dos games well into the 1997 era.
Plain awesome

Great! Not much else to say. Been running a buttery-smooth game of Master of Orion 2 for the past 2 weeks on and off, and without any issues or freezes.. If anything, I would like the touch emulation to improve a bit.

Would be awesome but I cant map certain keys to my keyboard or even the touch screen so I basically cant do a couple things and it's quite annoying, the left alt key is the biggest problem, not being able to use the shift key is another

I initially had some trouble installing the app, through no fault of the developer's (google play had an issue recognizing my purchase).  Installation issue resolved, the app runs VERY well and I am pleased to be able to run games like Elder Scrolls II : Daggerfall and Fallout on my tablet.  More than worth the price!
Warcraft 2 on tf700 works well, incl with real mouse.
I tried ADosBox and AnDosBox as well, and between the three, this is by far the best.  Well worth the four dollar pricetag.

While not for the casual user, this is a must have for any old school gamer. It takes some work, research, and trial & carrots error, but it's definitely worth it. The developer is very helpful and quick to respond to any questions.

I cannot believe that I have just played Jazz Jack Rabbit using a wii controller and doxbox turbo.........And with my Samsung Galaxy note it was so fast. Better than playing the original on pc. Once I had worked out how to map the control buttons it was really easy. Thumbs up for devs!

Ufo, dune2, syndicate tested. Absolute mouse tracking and scaling are worth the price alone. Though some of the text boxes are small and not designed for tablets. Fix that and it'll be an essential app for tablet gaming.
Some speed upgrades would be nice,and I'd love to have vibrating touch screen buttons just like its done in fpse - PlayStation emulator.
Keep up the good work!
Nuff said. ;)
It's playable! However, had to map volume control buttons to scrolling up and down because can't get the mouse to the exact top/bottom of the screen with absolute mouse tracking

This app is great - does what it promiss - it emulates a PC on the Android OS with "DOS". I was playing and setting up this for a lonng time (you have count with a longer time for tweaking because not everything works on default). I was able to run on it several DOS Games such as; ski or die, UFO, Dune 2 and others together with Fallout and Win95 :D

Best DOS emulator by far. The manager just makes it even better!  My only complaint is I can't get Carmageddon to run without stripes down the screen. It runs fine on my PC but no matter what graphics settings I use (in Dosbox Turbo or with the game itself launching in either low res or hi res) I get distorted graphics :(

I have really tried to like this but the truth is it's a buggy mess. For example, on default settings my nexus 7 runs the game "Blood" quite well yet the minute I try and do any configuring - change cpu cycles or cpu type - any game just hangs. Cpu cycles defaults to 3000, yet force 3000 in config and games hang. Change any setting and a restart app is required every time, why ? A lot more work is needed here, less bugs would be a start.
The best does emu out there. Worth the cost definitely.
Great app - easy to set up and fast, Panzer General on my phone is the best thing!
A must for all old PC gamers.

It does full speed emulation without any hassles and has some very useful preferences!  I'm so glad I got past my hesitation, since I had been using the other options.  This was so worth what little it cost!

I've got both xcom and MAX working on this and the absolute / relative mouse movement is exceptional and worth paying the money for. MAX isn't quite right with the new mouse gestures, but still perfectly useable.  Works full screen on the Nexus 10 which is also great. Brilliant product, thanks! :-)

Works very well on my Nexus 7. Daggerfall runs at average frame rate for a DOS game, but could be a bit smoother. Cyberdogs 2 & Assault Trooper run great also, and I'll probably test out Blood soon. Fishstix's Gamepad app also works great with everything so far. Thanks again man, my encouragements :)

This emulator is unbelievably good. The touchscreen absolute positioning option works and makes all the difference. That means that I can just tap a unit in strategy games, and tap its destination and it moves there. This feature alone has turned my tablet into an awesome gaming machine!

Well worth the cost. I tried the others and they just didn't work as well or have the features of this one. This DosBox works wonderfully with my TF300T hardware keyboard and track pad. I've started using a USB mouse and it brings me back to the original experience of these great DOS games.

I got this app to play Master of Orion II. It runs perfectly and i can click the in-game interface without any problems. It was almost like MO2 was made for touch devices! Thanks and keep up the good work!
Yes, finaly you implemented home/end, pgup/pgdown buttons. Great... 5 stars from me
Plays anything ive tested. Bit tricky to setup for some games.  Not apps fault though, some things just are.
It's frakin' dosbox!
Totally worth my money..
Just perfect.

Wow, I was very skeptical this would play time commando, a game from 1997 that requires a 486 but it did run. It really does run like the pc dosbox. I'm really amazed and excited. The greatest thing is that in the game's intro video someone plays the game itself on a tablet that looks super futuristic hahahaha.
Couldn't be happier with this optimized version of DOSbox. The control implementations are brilliant and the "absolute" mouse pointer works a treat for RTS titles.
Finally I have found something that lets me play my old favourite and on my Nexus 7, of all things. Awesome.
Runs much quicker than other dos emulators, a great purchase
Compiled my own dos-programs. After some fiddling I got it running!
Works with everything I've tried so far.
The best Dosbox implementation on Android!
This is the best software I have ever installed. I played Master of Magic for 8 hours straight on a long plane flight!

It's been a long a time since absolute mouse positioning has been in experimental state. Coordinates are determined incorrectly on both  Samsung Galaxy Note 10.1 and SE XPeria Ray. For  the first it's especially upsetting since it has a stylus. Otherwise great application.
Excellent performance and very easy to use.  Only complaint is that you have to go to manual configuration mode to get PC speaker emulation back, but the dev says he's fixing that.
Perfect!   Developer is also quick to answer questions!

App allows me to play all my favorite DOS games including Full Throttle, Indiana Jones, Day of the Tentacle, Daggerfall, Lords of the Realm, Monkey Island, Doom, Simon the Sorcerer, and many many more! Read up on mounting, try different game settings and you are in the game. Only issue I found was no easy way to restart DOSbox to save settings, even though it tells you to restart!
Great emulator, plays everything well so far.  Would like to be able to map "delete" and "insert" keys in future update.
Hard to use

It just simply does what it's supposed to do.  Run Dos apps and run the well.    Only a couple of things I would like to see is more options exposed in the GUI as opposed to editing them in the config. One such feature is PC Speaker activation. I had to turn on manual mode and edit the config file (setting PC Speaker to TRUE) to hear sound on games that didn't use a sound card.    The other thing I'd LOVE to see is compatibility with the "Swype" keyboard.  Regardless, still giving it 5 stars.

Title says it all,  just need a basic understanding of dos which i picked up in 20 mins, The Manager makes it very easy and also looks good, I have 10 games currently installed, Some games work as if they were designed for touchscreen when using the Absolute Tracking for example, Syndicate, Xcom, Eye of the beholder they all work just by tapping the screen were you want to click works extremely well, Just need some way of clicking both left and right mouse button at the same time using touch gesture as some games require it.  Amazing  Dan
This is a great app with great support. I literally had a issue with my touchscreen not responding as mouse in game and within 2 minutes had a email back with a solution.

Was a bit wary of purchasing without testing first as other android dos emulators haven't worked on my phone, but gladly Turbo works fine. Haven't come across any DOS games that I've not been able to run using this app. Another plus is that Turbo's got a profile manager app as well, which is quite a handy feature.

I recently finished playing Discworld on my Nexus 7 and I have to say that this app is incredible. Not only does it have a great amount of configuration including hardware key remapping (I remapped my volume up key for ESC to exit dialog and my volume down to F1 to call the menu) but the Dev support is top notch too. As I said when I emailed the developer, I would love to see support to hide jellybeans soft keys but he explained the problem with that to me and the reason it was currently not viable. Thanks!

Opens up a world of old PC games, particularly classic RPGs. Very nice interface and options, developer is responsive to feedback which is superb. I heartily recommend this app for those wanting to try out some old DOS games. Just check the compatibility list first. Awesome stuff.

Within this emulator, Master of Magic plays well on both a Samsung Galaxy Nexus and a 1GHz single core generic tablet.  Using the "absolute" mouse tracking and double tap for right click it feels almost like a native android game.  You'll want to also install the fee DosBox Turbo Manager, although for some odd reason it's not compatible with my generic tablet even though DosBox Turbo itself is.
Great app. I'm playing Master of Orion. So cool!
Works brilliantly with sixaxis and a ps3 controller, allows mapping any button to any game key. Pretty easy to set up and runs old games very well.

I came from andosbox to DOSBox Turbo and I'm finding it alot easier to use and getting MIDI support as well as a manager app for your games is quite an advantage. The manager app saves the preferences and auto executive instructions for each game. Plus the gamepad that the DOSBox Turbo company made really works well for a beta.  Above all it is really great and runs daggerfall very well.  I feel like I got more than my moneys worth for the price. :) also the gamepad he offers can turn into a keyboard.
Best dosbox ported to android available...absolutely worth the $$$

I downloaded this with the hopes of getting Arena and Daggerfall running on my VZW GS3 and by God it did. It took a lot for me to figure out how to do this because there really aren't any in depth guides for it but I finally managed to do it on my own. This is easily the best Dos emulator on the market. It runs Daggerfall on the default settings and with the CPU set to ondemand, albeit a little slow. Once the CPU is set to Performance in SetCPU and you tweak a few values it runs without a hitch. Great job!!
Runs pretty smooth while I'm playing Elder Scrolls Arena. Best Dos on the market! Samsung Infuse.

Our top App purchase to date by a distance is the wonderful DosBox Turbo at just Â£2.49. This solitary buy has opened up a huge array of our great DOS games collection on the N7, including our all time favourite's XCom and Command & Conquer. Touch screen gameplay has been integrated into DB-Turbo enhancing the playability innumerately. Touch is not perfectly implemented yet, but with auto updates enabled this superb software is only going to improve. DB-T is a hugely recommended purchase that opens up a fantastic range of classic titles. All of which look suitably prim and proud on the N7's vibrant compact screen.

I'm running Dosbox turbo on Samsung Tab2 10.1.  It runs great, but I'm running out of room in my sdcard, and it didn't recognize when I tried to mount my extsdcard, or usb flash drive. Does anyone know how to mount those? Thanks.  Updates: I figured how to mount those mount f /mnt/extSdCard/ -t cdrom  Thanks anyway :)
I got Fallout on my phone!! Love the mouse emulation! Great buy! Please make key assignments for the keypad.

Very lovely app but some game doesnt works perfectly example prince of persia 1 is running but the character doesnt move so its unplayable.But i love this app and finally i can customize the buttons in my xplay
This is a truley excellent emulator, it does its job very well. The only thing that could improve it is a suspend function, losing your progress when someone calls is no fun.

This is by far one of the best apps to install on your android device. It works perfectly and allows you to relive the best gaming moments of your past - nostalgia at its best! Add to that, great support from the developer if you have any questions - 5 stars well earned.

Ill give this 5 stars when i can collab my wiimote with the emulator, it has like 3 options for controllers and isnt wiimote friendly.  This would be perfect if i could use my controller because everything else about it is flawless.

Playing XCom UFO Defense on my Galaxy S3. Runs without a hitch. Simple to set up. Mouse support is okay. Has support for direct touch for clicking on things, but I can't scroll up or down in tactical mode. Trackpad mode works well enough. I bound left / right click to volume up / down, so I have physical buttons for those. No midi support, but I'm not shedding any tears.

Nexus 7 emulates approx Pentium 75-90 MHz, tried Duke 3d runs perfect. Use with dosbox manager frontend add on (free), very convenient. Patience required initially to set up, lots of documentation on web. Well worth Â£2.49, hope author keeps it updated

DOSbox Turbo is great, AnDosBox sucks. End of Review! That basically sums it up and now for the expanded review for those that interested. I congratulate Fishstix for staying with their labour of love and continuing to develop this awesome emulator and now that I am moving on soon to the Note 2 I can only expect more greatness in speed increases (due to processor) and screen and I can leave this into the hands of someone who is going to continue to make this even better. As for AnDosBox, it used to be a good emulator but recent dick moves by the developer of AnDosBox against DosBox Turbo is childish and petty. I own both emus and would have like AnDosBox to have been continued to be developed like DosBox Turbo since they both had their own strengths but as it is DosBox Turbo is now the All-In-One package and add to the extra free addons to this and it really shines. I have played through Hoboken, Shannara, Legacy, AITD, UFO and I am still trying to get Fallout to run without a hitch but maybe that will happen with a new phone :P This is a terrific port and any DosBox aficionado should not miss it!!
Being able to play my old DOS games on the Nexus 7 is fantastic!
great emulator
Works great. Runs Dungeon Keeper and World of Xeen very smoothly. Better than my old 486. The on screen mouse works especially well for mouse driven games with large icons.
Great app! Cool Dev.
Anything that allows me to play the settlers in svga mode on my dell streak this smoothly deserves 5 stars and more! Thank you very much.
Wonderful app. I'm amazed by how smoothly some of the programs run. Now if only touch screens were conducive to nostalgic keyboard video games. Adventure games are fun though!
Awesome app.

This app is great, very simple to use and seems to run nearly everything I throw at it.  This isn't really a grope at this app, but I'd love for there to be a an android "keyboard" which uses the phones acceleromator to emulate a joystick... is there something like this already out there?  There's a few that tether to a pc or other droid device.... even better if it was inbuilt into Turbo!  Cheers y'all!

I downloaded all the DOS games I remember owning and love this. Takes time to figure out some of the controls but they work great. Ultima 6,Ultima 7, Jones in the Fast Lane, Xcom 1 & 2, still working on getting Wing Commander to work. But they all seem to run flawlessly.   I use this on a Coby Kyros Android tablet.  You need DOSBox Manager if you have this. Makes selecting games a snap.
Very easy to use and with great features! So far I have played Syndicate and Fallout with no problems. Definitely sets the standard for DoS emulation.
I can play Quest for Glory on a handheld device. Thanks, guy(s)! :D

I had a problem, emailed support.l, they answered with a question then ignored my response. Its buggy and controls are broken for some games. Adosbox is better! DONT PAY MONEY WHEN THERES ZERO SUPPORT!
replyContent: I'm sorry if we missed your e-mail.  We strive to respond to all questions within 48 hours.  Please write us with your problem and I will personally respond.

content: Works great for most games but turrican 2 sadly doesn't work. Great Work overall Though!
Amazing, this works great and now I can use and play the programs and games I played so long ago! it even has an option for mouse pad tracking from the Transformer series, superb!

First app store review ever posted.  Never before has the difference between a free and paid app been so significant.  Even if you aren't familiar with dosbox, this makes it easy lemon squeezy.  One of the best purchases for my nexus 7.  Also look at scummvm for your scumm engine games.
Best emulator I've tried so far. Keep up the good work

I have tried all the other dosbox apps out there, and this is for sure the best. I loved it on my droidx and now I love it even more on my xperia play. Buy it! Nothing like Dark Forces and Jazz Jackrabbit
Works perfectly, absolutely astounding.

I've been using it for a few days and i have to say it is much faster than any other open source or paid solutions. Warcraft2, Dungeon Keeper, UFO, Civ.... all works perfectly! It has also a much richer set of features than others, and the support is fantastic! I wrote two letters with some issues and got proper answers and solutions within hours...  if DOS and Android it is The Right Choice!  Please note however that on Asus Transformers crashes sometimes but that is an Asus ICS bug, does not belong to this app

All of my favorite DOS games from years ago run great.  I love the old turn-based wargames like Steel Panthers 1 & 2, Panzer General, etc. and was pleased to find they all work!  Highly recommend this.

I've used adosbox and andosbox, and one other I think.  This DosBox Turbo is, by far, the fastest.  I can play doom easily.  It will even play Quake 1 (at low res setting).  It is worth every penny if you got a lot of old DOS games that you are pining to play.  (I am using a ASUS Transformer Prime - with an NVIDIA quad-core Tegra T30 chip).
Truly fantastic app. Plays all my favourite old pc games.
Great. Thank you!

Now I can play Civilization II whenever and wherever I want. :)  The only issue I have is that the joystick seems to need a bit more work, for example I cannot get it working properly in Commander Keen. Aside from that, it's totally worth the price.
Crashes every 1 - 10 minutes. Also fails "license check" and caps CPU cycles once in a while (probably when there's no Internet connection). I think it has a lot of potential so 4 stars.
I'm works well but I can't get Red Alert working at all (user error). Thanks for the consistent updates.

I've used DOSBOX for years on my Macbook and my expectations for something similar on my Captivate was low.  But it works great!  I've been playing Leisure Suit Larry 2, one of my favorites, on my phone.  If you phone lacks a physical keyboard I highly suggest a Bluetooth keyboard, but it's not absolutely required.  Definitely worth the price!
works great

Awesome app.  I use the manager too.  I dug out all my old games... Shannara, Master of Orion 2, Quake, and Descent. Very helpful and quick to respond to questions. I have also found that the hackers keyboard to invaluable to use with this app.
I Can play all of my old games. Warcraft 2, Colonization and Pizza Tycoon! All with real mouse support! This app rocks!!!
Extremely good emulator and the developer is quick to respond if you have trouble
It's rock solid stable for almost everything you throw at it, I am a few hours into fallout.  Needs a better option for platformers like Keen and Duke though for controls.

This is an EXCELLENT port of DOSBox for Android - by far the best available. It has tons of great features for tweaking speed, graphical/audio quality, and interaction with each specific game. It also has an excellent manager app similar to D-Fend Reloaded for PC which allows you to setup separate profiles for each game so you don't have to type it all in each time - it does require some initial setup, and I think it could use some improvement in this regard, but once you're done, it's great. For those of us who really know what we're doing with Dosbox, there is even a manual mode for creating individual .conf files for each game to tweak them beyond the variables that are changable via the Dosbox Turbo UI. This is great for me because this is the only way to hit the "sweet spot" on a few of my games because audio pre-buffer, block size, and sample rate aren't currently editable via the UI. Perhaps best of all, this app has an awesome developer who I have spoken with several times - he is very receptive to feedback and every feature I've requested has either later been implemented (custom icons for the manager) or has been promised to be in subsequent updates (prebuffer). 5 stars!
